    "claim": "When `getBalanceForPool(pool)` is zero, `poolCheckpoint()` skips `_updateEarned()` entirely, so `lastHoldings` is not advanced even though Convex/CNC rewards keep accruing. The next account that stakes any amount and triggers `_accountCheckpoint()` causes the full historical backlog to be divided by the new nonzero staked supply, letting that account capture rewards that accrued while nobody was staked.",
    "impact": "A dust staker can drain all accumulated CRV, CVX, and CNC rewards from a pool after an unstaked interval, stealing rewards that should have been retained or socialized rather than assigned entirely to the first subsequent staker.",
    "paths": [
      "All LP stakers exit or unstake so `getBalanceForPool(pool) == 0` while Curve/Convex/CNC rewards continue accruing.",
      "Attacker deposits a minimal amount and stakes LP tokens.",
      "Attacker calls `claimEarnings()` or any path that triggers `_accountCheckpoint()`.",
      "The previously unaccounted reward backlog is allocated against the attacker's tiny staked balance and can then be claimed."
    ]
  },
