    "claim": "`_setWeightToZero()` rescales the remaining weights with floor rounding, so their sum can become slightly less than 1e18. While `rebalancingRewardActive` is true, `_getMaxDeviation()` returns zero and `_depositToCurve()` requires every deposited wei to fit into some pool's exact target allocation; once the rounding residue exceeds the hardcoded 100-unit tolerance, `_getDepositPool()` finds no eligible pool and the deposit reverts.",
    "impact": "After permissionless depeg handling or invalid-PID handling, large pools can enter a state where new deposits are denied until governance/controller performs a manual weight reset, degrading availability exactly during emergency rebalancing.",
